---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import CTA from "../components/CTA.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Manifesto"
  description="The principle, and the four values FeedForwardClub tries to hold as the room grows."
  ogType="article"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Manifesto</span>
      <h1>What we try to <em class="accent">hold.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">
        These are not rules. They are the standards we keep reminding
        ourselves of, especially as the room grows and it becomes easier to
        forget.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule" />

  

  <hr class="rule" />

  <!-- VALUES -->
  <section class="section manifesto">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Culture</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Four things we try to get right.</h2>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">I.</span>
          <h3>Bias, almost not.</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          The world is a ratchet: winners become more-winners. Capital finds
          capital. Attention finds attention. The already-funded get funded
          faster than the first-time founder with the better idea.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not pretend to fix that. We refuse to replicate it in this
          room. The composition is
          <strong>roughly 60% non-winners and 40% winners</strong>, on
          purpose. When that ratio flips, we recalibrate. A room where the
          established voice is always the loudest is a room that teaches
          everyone to sound established instead of <em>right</em>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">II.</span>
          <h3>No racism. No sexism. No gatekeeping.</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          Zero tolerance, no negotiation, no "it was a joke". The room is
          too small and the work too important to let any of it in.
        </p>
        <p>
          Yes, previous accomplishments matter. We are not pretending
          otherwise. They simply matter <em>less</em> here than they do
          outside. What we pay attention to is
          <span class="mark">your obsession</span> and
          <span class="mark">your value proposition</span>. What are you
          unreasonably fixated on, and who does it help?
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">III.</span>
          <h3>Be genuine. Be respectful.</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          Blunt is allowed. Cruel is not. If your advice would be
          useful to a friend at the exact stage this person is at, say it.
          If it is only useful for making yourself sound clever, keep it to
          yourself.
        </p>
    
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">IV.</span>
          <h3>No hierarchy</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          In the long run, this club should run on its culture, not on its
          founder. No one needs another founder-cult.
        </p>
        <p>
          In the early days, <strong>@yeargun</strong> makes sure the culture
          sets properly and the standards stay high: picks the room, defends
          the values, calls out drift. Not because he knows best, but because
          someone has to hold the line while the habits set in. When the
          culture holds itself, that role goes away.
        </p>
      </article>

      <p class="sign">— FeedForwardClub</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule" />


</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
  .hero {
    padding: clamp(72px, 10vw, 140px) 0 clamp(32px, 5vw, 64px);

    .lede { max-width: 680px; margin-top: 16px; }
    h1 em.accent { font-style: italic; color: $accent; }
  }

  // — preamble ---------------------------------------------------------------
  .preamble .container { max-width: 780px; }

  .preamble-card {
    padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
    background: $paper;
    border: 1px solid $rule;
    border-left: 4px solid $accent;
    border-radius: $radius-lg;

    .tag-label {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: $fs-meta;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: $accent-deep;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    h2 { margin: 0 0 24px; }

    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: $ink-soft;
    }

    strong { color: $ink; font-weight: 600; }
    strong.forward { color: $amber-deep; font-style: italic; }
  }

  // — values -----------------------------------------------------------------
  .manifesto .container { max-width: 760px; }

  .section-title { margin-bottom: 24px; }

  .entry {
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid $rule;

    &:last-of-type { border-bottom: 0; }

    header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 12px 16px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    @media (max-width: $bp-sm) {
      header {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }
    }

    .num {
      font-family: $font-serif;
      font-size: 26px;
      color: $accent;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    h3 { margin: 0; font-size: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 28px); }

    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: $ink-soft;
    }
  }

  .sign {
    font-family: $font-serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: $ink;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .cta-section {
    text-align: left;
    background: $paper;
    border-top: 1px solid $rule;
    border-bottom: 1px solid $rule;
  }
</style>
